The paper deals with computer vision tasks such as semantic labelling and instance segmentation, which are typically studied in the computer vision subfield (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a novel approach to weakly supervised learning, which is a topic of interest in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of bounding box detection annotations and convolutional neural networks (convnets) also suggests that the paper may be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and natural language processing (cs.CL) subfields.
